Embu assembly speaker Justus Kariuki has said he will resign if found liable over the alleged Sh335 million office complex s construction scandal.Assembly clerk Jim Kauma has also been questioned over the procurement for construction of a five-storey office complex for MCAs.He said he would resign if found guilty of corruption.Kyeni North MCA Kanjogu Mugo kick-started the investigations after petitioning the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission to probe the tendering. Mugo said the procurement was flawed and violated the law. Those questioned over the last three weeks are the speaker, clerk and more than 20 assembly staff.Others are engineers from the Public Works docket led by project manager Frederick Ndaire.